            <div type="summary">
                <head type="summary" tid="1">Summary</head>
                <milestone unit="chunk" xml:id="UT22084-063-001-1"/>
                <p tid="2">In the Deer Park in Vārānasī, an extended dialogue unfolds between Buddha
                    Śākyamuni and his disciple Śāriputra on the faults and unwanted consequences
                    associated with the corrupted discipline of monks, and on the ways to apply
                    oneself to the authentic Dharma. While discussing a variety of topics related to
                    monastic conduct, the Buddha gives several prophecies about the future decline
                    of the Dharma caused by the behavior of immoral monks. Throughout the sūtra,
                    great emphasis is placed on the realization of the nature of emptiness and the
                    view that does not dwell on any phenomenon. </p>
            </div>
